        "title": "How Indexes Work",
        "text": "<p>Without indexes, every query requires a <strong>full table scan</strong> � reading every row, taking hours on a billion-row table. An <strong>index</strong> (usually a B-tree) maps values to row locations, reducing lookup from O(n) to O(log n).</p>\n          <p>The trade-off: faster reads come at the cost of slower writes, since every index must be updated on each INSERT or UPDATE.</p>",
